{
  "video_id": "qaIghx4QRN4",
  "title": "Where are all the aliens? | Stephen Webb",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 13200.0,
      "end_time": 15376.0,
      "text": "I saw a UFO once."
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 15400.0,
      "end_time": 17296.0,
      "text": "I was eight or nine,"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 17320.0,
      "end_time": 20656.0,
      "text": "playing in the street with a friend who was a couple of years older,"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 20680.0,
      "end_time": 25336.0,
      "text": "and we saw a featureless silver disc hovering over the houses."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 25360.0,
      "end_time": 27136.0,
      "text": "We watched it for a few seconds,"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 27160.0,
      "end_time": 30416.0,
      "text": "and then it shot away incredibly quickly."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 30440.0,
      "end_time": 31656.0,
      "text": "Even as a kid,"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 31680.0,
      "end_time": 34519.0,
      "text": "I got angry it was ignoring the laws of physics."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 35160.0,
      "end_time": 37416.0,
      "text": "We ran inside to tell the grown-ups,"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 37440.0,
      "end_time": 39160.0,
      "text": "and they were skeptical --"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 39400.0,
      "end_time": 41120.0,
      "text": "you&#39;d be skeptical too, right?"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 42120.0,
      "end_time": 43855.0,
      "text": "I got my own back a few years later:"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 43880.0,
      "end_time": 45376.0,
      "text": "one of those grown-ups told me,"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 45400.0,
      "end_time": 47216.0,
      "text": "\"Last night I saw a flying saucer."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 47240.0,
      "end_time": 49816.0,
      "text": "I was coming out of the pub after a few drinks.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 49840.0,
      "end_time": 52656.0,
      "text": "I stopped him there. I said, \"I can explain that sighting.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 52680.0,
      "end_time": 53696.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 53720.0,
      "end_time": 56616.0,
      "text": "Psychologists have shown we can&#39;t trust our brains"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 56640.0,
      "end_time": 57856.0,
      "text": "to tell the truth."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 57880.0,
      "end_time": 59696.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s easy to fool ourselves."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 59720.0,
      "end_time": 61336.0,
      "text": "I saw something,"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 61360.0,
      "end_time": 62736.0,
      "text": "but what&#39;s more likely --"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 62760.0,
      "end_time": 64775.0,
      "text": "that I saw an alien spacecraft,"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 64800.0,
      "end_time": 68720.0,
      "text": "or that my brain misinterpreted the data my eyes were giving it?"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 70200.0,
      "end_time": 71776.0,
      "text": "Ever since though I&#39;ve wondered:"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 71800.0,
      "end_time": 74816.0,
      "text": "Why don&#39;t we see flying saucers flitting around?"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 74840.0,
      "end_time": 76560.0,
      "text": "At the very least,"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 76800.0,
      "end_time": 78936.0,
      "text": "why don&#39;t we see life out there in the cosmos?"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 78960.0,
      "end_time": 80175.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a puzzle,"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 80200.0,
      "end_time": 82656.0,
      "text": "and I&#39;ve discussed it with dozens of experts"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 82680.0,
      "end_time": 85816.0,
      "text": "from different disciplines over the past three decades."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 85840.0,
      "end_time": 87696.0,
      "text": "And there&#39;s no consensus."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 87720.0,
      "end_time": 92560.0,
      "text": "Frank Drake began searching for alien signals back in 1960 --"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 92800.0,
      "end_time": 93976.0,
      "text": "so far, nothing."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 94000.0,
      "end_time": 95416.0,
      "text": "And with each passing year,"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 95440.0,
      "end_time": 96976.0,
      "text": "this nonobservation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 97000.0,
      "end_time": 102656.0,
      "text": "this lack of evidence for any alien activity gets more puzzling"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 102680.0,
      "end_time": 105680.0,
      "text": "because we should see them, shouldn&#39;t we?"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 107120.0,
      "end_time": 110896.0,
      "text": "The universe is 13.8 billion years old,"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 110920.0,
      "end_time": 112176.0,
      "text": "give or take."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 112200.0,
      "end_time": 115696.0,
      "text": "If we represent the age of the universe by one year,"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 115720.0,
      "end_time": 120295.0,
      "text": "then our species came into being about 12 minutes before midnight,"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 120320.0,
      "end_time": 121559.0,
      "text": "31st December."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 122120.0,
      "end_time": 125776.0,
      "text": "Western civilization has existed for a few seconds."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 125800.0,
      "end_time": 129520.0,
      "text": "Extraterrestrial civilizations could have started in the summer months."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 130600.0,
      "end_time": 133335.0,
      "text": "Imagine a summer civilization"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 133360.0,
      "end_time": 137616.0,
      "text": "developing a level of technology more advanced than ours,"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 137640.0,
      "end_time": 139775.0,
      "text": "but tech based on accepted physics though,"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 139800.0,
      "end_time": 143736.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m not talking wormholes or warp drives -- whatever --"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 143760.0,
      "end_time": 148280.0,
      "text": "just an extrapolation of the sort of tech that TED celebrates."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 148880.0,
      "end_time": 152456.0,
      "text": "That civilization could program self-replicating probes"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 152480.0,
      "end_time": 155119.0,
      "text": "to visit every planetary system in the galaxy."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 155840.0,
      "end_time": 160360.0,
      "text": "If they launched the first probes just after midnight one August day,"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 161200.0,
      "end_time": 163456.0,
      "text": "then before breakfast same day,"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 163480.0,
      "end_time": 165600.0,
      "text": "they could have colonized the galaxy."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 166640.0,
      "end_time": 169215.0,
      "text": "Intergalactic colonization isn&#39;t much more difficult,"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 169240.0,
      "end_time": 170480.0,
      "text": "it just takes longer."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 171800.0,
      "end_time": 174160.0,
      "text": "A civilization from any one of millions of galaxies"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 174400.0,
      "end_time": 176400.0,
      "text": "could have colonized our galaxy."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 176960.0,
      "end_time": 178696.0,
      "text": "Seems far-fetched?"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 178720.0,
      "end_time": 179936.0,
      "text": "Maybe it is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 179960.0,
      "end_time": 185560.0,
      "text": "but wouldn&#39;t aliens engage in some recognizable activity --"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 185800.0,
      "end_time": 189336.0,
      "text": "put worldlets around a star to capture free sunlight,"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 189360.0,
      "end_time": 192536.0,
      "text": "collaborate on a Wikipedia Galactica,"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 192560.0,
      "end_time": 195480.0,
      "text": "or just shout out to the universe, \"We&#39;re here\"?"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 196920.0,
      "end_time": 198119.0,
      "text": "So where is everybody?"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 198760.0,
      "end_time": 204176.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a puzzle because we do expect these civilizations to exist, don&#39;t we?"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 204200.0,
      "end_time": 207375.0,
      "text": "After all, there could be a trillion planets in the galaxy --"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 207400.0,
      "end_time": 208760.0,
      "text": "maybe more."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 209600.0,
      "end_time": 213976.0,
      "text": "You don&#39;t need any special knowledge to consider this question,"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 214000.0,
      "end_time": 217896.0,
      "text": "and I&#39;ve explored it with lots of people over the years."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 217920.0,
      "end_time": 220896.0,
      "text": "And I&#39;ve found they often frame their thinking"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 220920.0,
      "end_time": 224160.0,
      "text": "in terms of the barriers that would need to be cleared"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 224400.0,
      "end_time": 228280.0,
      "text": "if a planet is to host a communicative civilization."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 229120.0,
      "end_time": 232936.0,
      "text": "And they usually identify four key barriers."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 232960.0,
      "end_time": 234336.0,
      "text": "Habitability --"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 234360.0,
      "end_time": 235776.0,
      "text": "that&#39;s the first barrier."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 235800.0,
      "end_time": 240416.0,
      "text": "We need a terrestrial planet in that just right \"Goldilocks zone,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 240440.0,
      "end_time": 242680.0,
      "text": "where water flows as a liquid."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 243400.0,
      "end_time": 244656.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re out there."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 244680.0,
      "end_time": 249256.0,
      "text": "In 2016, astronomers confirmed there&#39;s a planet in the habitable zone"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 249280.0,
      "end_time": 250736.0,
      "text": "of the closest star,"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 250760.0,
      "end_time": 252536.0,
      "text": "Proxima Centauri --"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 252560.0,
      "end_time": 257616.0,
      "text": "so close that Breakthrough Starshot project plans to send probes there."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 257640.0,
      "end_time": 260519.0,
      "text": "We&#39;d become a starfaring species."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 261480.00000000003,
      "end_time": 263960.0,
      "text": "But not all worlds are habitable."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 263120.0,
      "end_time": 265456.0,
      "text": "Some will be too close to a star and they&#39;ll fry,"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 265480.0,
      "end_time": 267600.0,
      "text": "some will be too far away and they&#39;ll freeze."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 268800.0,
      "end_time": 270160.0,
      "text": "Abiogenesis --"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 270400.0,
      "end_time": 271815.0,
      "text": "the creation of life from nonlife --"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 271839.0,
      "end_time": 273120.0,
      "text": "that&#39;s the second barrier."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 274000.0,
      "end_time": 277896.0,
      "text": "The basic building blocks of life aren&#39;t unique to Earth:"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 277920.0,
      "end_time": 280656.0,
      "text": "amino acids have been found in comets,"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 280680.0,
      "end_time": 283776.0,
      "text": "complex organic molecules in interstellar dust clouds,"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 283800.0,
      "end_time": 286400.0,
      "text": "water in exoplanetary systems."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 287160.0,
      "end_time": 288416.0,
      "text": "The ingredients are there,"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 288440.0,
      "end_time": 291960.0,
      "text": "we just don&#39;t know how they combine to create life,"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 291120.0,
      "end_time": 294280.0,
      "text": "and presumably there will be worlds on which life doesn&#39;t start."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 295840.0,
      "end_time": 299520.0,
      "text": "The development of technological civilization is a third barrier."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 300600.0,
      "end_time": 305376.0,
      "text": "Some say we already share our planet with alien intelligences."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 305400.0,
      "end_time": 310200.0,
      "text": "A 2011 study showed that elephants can cooperate to solve problems."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 310840.0,
      "end_time": 312376.0,
      "text": "A 2010 study showed"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 312400.0,
      "end_time": 316679.0,
      "text": "that an octopus in captivity can recognize different humans."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 317360.0,
      "end_time": 321256.0,
      "text": "2017 studies show that ravens can plan for future events --"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 321280.0,
      "end_time": 324150.0,
      "text": "wonderful, clever creatures --"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 324400.0,
      "end_time": 327256.0,
      "text": "but they can&#39;t contemplate the Breakthrough Starshot project,"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 327280.0,
      "end_time": 329535.0,
      "text": "and if we vanished today,"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 329560.0,
      "end_time": 332416.0,
      "text": "they wouldn&#39;t go on to implement Breakthrough Starshot --"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 332440.0,
      "end_time": 333816.0,
      "text": "why should they?"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 333840.0,
      "end_time": 336599.0,
      "text": "Evolution doesn&#39;t have space travel as an end goal."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 337160.0,
      "end_time": 341720.0,
      "text": "There will be worlds where life doesn&#39;t give rise to advanced technology."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 343400.0,
      "end_time": 345896.0,
      "text": "Communication across space -- that&#39;s a fourth barrier."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 345920.0,
      "end_time": 349696.0,
      "text": "Maybe advanced civilizations choose to explore inner space"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 349720.0,
      "end_time": 352560.0,
      "text": "rather than outer space,"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 352800.0,
      "end_time": 355599.0,
      "text": "or engineer at small distances rather than large."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 356600.0,
      "end_time": 359456.0,
      "text": "Or maybe they just don&#39;t want to risk an encounter"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 359480.0,
      "end_time": 363616.0,
      "text": "with a potentially more advanced and hostile neighbor."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 363640.0,
      "end_time": 365816.0,
      "text": "There&#39;ll be worlds where, for whatever reason,"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 365840.0,
      "end_time": 370479.0,
      "text": "civilizations either stay silent or don&#39;t spend long trying to communicate."
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 372600.0,
      "end_time": 374696.0,
      "text": "As for the height of the barriers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 374720.0,
      "end_time": 377120.0,
      "text": "your guess is as good as anyone&#39;s."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 378800.0,
      "end_time": 379335.0,
      "text": "In my experience,"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 379360.0,
      "end_time": 381416.0,
      "text": "when people sit down and do the math,"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 381440.0,
      "end_time": 386320.0,
      "text": "they typically conclude there are thousands of civilizations in the galaxy."
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 387640.0,
      "end_time": 390360.0,
      "text": "But then we&#39;re back to the puzzle: Where is everybody?"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 392550.0,
      "end_time": 393416.0,
      "text": "By definition,"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 393440.0,
      "end_time": 395776.0,
      "text": "UFOs -- including the one I saw --"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 395800.0,
      "end_time": 397960.0,
      "text": "are unidentified."
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 397120.0,
      "end_time": 400856.0,
      "text": "We can&#39;t simply infer they&#39;re spacecraft."
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 400880.0,
      "end_time": 404360.0,
      "text": "You can still have some fun playing with the idea aliens are here."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 405000.0,
      "end_time": 408856.0,
      "text": "Some say a summer civilization did colonize the galaxy"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 408880.0,
      "end_time": 410880.0,
      "text": "and seeded Earth with life ..."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 411800.0,
      "end_time": 414656.0,
      "text": "others, that we&#39;re living in a cosmic wilderness preserve --"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 414680.0,
      "end_time": 415920.0,
      "text": "a zoo."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 416480.0,
      "end_time": 417976.0,
      "text": "Yet others --"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 418000.0,
      "end_time": 420176.0,
      "text": "that we&#39;re living in a simulation."
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 420200.0,
      "end_time": 422520.0,
      "text": "Programmers just haven&#39;t revealed the aliens yet."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 423680.0,
      "end_time": 428160.0,
      "text": "Most of my colleagues though argue that E.T. is out there,"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 428400.0,
      "end_time": 429656.0,
      "text": "we just need to keep looking,"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 429680.0,
      "end_time": 431256.0,
      "text": "and this makes sense."
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 431280.0,
      "end_time": 433560.0,
      "text": "Space is vast."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 433800.0,
      "end_time": 435895.0,
      "text": "Identifying a signal is hard,"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 435920.0,
      "end_time": 438520.0,
      "text": "and we haven&#39;t been looking that long."
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 439160.0,
      "end_time": 442296.0,
      "text": "Without doubt, we should spend more on the search."
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 442320.0,
      "end_time": 445656.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s about understanding our place in the universe."
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 445680.0,
      "end_time": 449000.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s too important a question to ignore."
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 449840.0,
      "end_time": 451936.0,
      "text": "But there&#39;s an obvious answer:"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 451960.0,
      "end_time": 453256.0,
      "text": "we&#39;re alone."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 453280.0,
      "end_time": 454895.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s just us."
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 454920.0,
      "end_time": 458416.0,
      "text": "There could be a trillion planets in the galaxy."
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 458440.0,
      "end_time": 462920.0,
      "text": "Is it plausible we&#39;re the only creatures capable of contemplating this question?"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 463840.0,
      "end_time": 466455.0,
      "text": "Well, yes, because in this context,"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 466480.0,
      "end_time": 468840.0,
      "text": "we don&#39;t know whether a trillion is a big number."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 470400.0,
      "end_time": 475336.0,
      "text": "In 2000, Peter Ward and Don Brownlee proposed the Rare Earth idea."
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 475360.0,
      "end_time": 477176.0,
      "text": "Remember those four barriers"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 477200.0,
      "end_time": 481560.0,
      "text": "that people use to estimate the number of civilizations?"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 481800.0,
      "end_time": 483200.0,
      "text": "Ward and Brownlee said there might be more."
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 483840.0,
      "end_time": 485536.0,
      "text": "Let&#39;s look at one possible barrier."
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 485560.0,
      "end_time": 488216.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a recent suggestion by David Waltham,"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 488240.0,
      "end_time": 489480.0,
      "text": "a geophysicist."
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 490000.0,
      "end_time": 492456.0,
      "text": "This is my very simplified version"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 492480.0,
      "end_time": 495800.0,
      "text": "of Dave&#39;s much more sophisticated argument."
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 496240.0,
      "end_time": 498256.0,
      "text": "We are able to be here now"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 498280.0,
      "end_time": 500936.0,
      "text": "because Earth&#39;s previous inhabitants enjoyed"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 500960.0,
      "end_time": 503135.0,
      "text": "four billion years of good weather --"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 503160.0,
      "end_time": 505800.0,
      "text": "ups and downs but more or less clement."
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 506960.0,
      "end_time": 509455.0,
      "text": "But long-term climate stability is strange,"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 509480.0,
      "end_time": 511896.0,
      "text": "if only because astronomical influences"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 511920.0,
      "end_time": 515976.0,
      "text": "can push a planet towards freezing or frying."
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 516000.0,
      "end_time": 518176.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s a hint our moon has helped,"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 518200.00000000006,
      "end_time": 520376.00000000006,
      "text": "and that&#39;s interesting"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 520400.0,
      "end_time": 522550.0,
      "text": "because the prevailing theory is"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 522799.99999999994,
      "end_time": 524576.0,
      "text": "that the moon came into being when Theia,"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 524600.0,
      "end_time": 526216.0,
      "text": "a body the size of Mars,"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 526240.0,
      "end_time": 528976.0,
      "text": "crashed into a newly formed Earth."
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 529000.0,
      "end_time": 533120.0,
      "text": "The outcome of that crash could have been a quite different Earth-Moon system."
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 534120.0,
      "end_time": 536376.0,
      "text": "We ended up with a large moon"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 536400.0,
      "end_time": 540256.0,
      "text": "and that permitted Earth to have both a stable axial tilt"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 540280.0,
      "end_time": 543456.0,
      "text": "and a slow rotation rate."
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 543480.0,
      "end_time": 545136.0,
      "text": "Both factors influence climate"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 545160.0,
      "end_time": 548760.0,
      "text": "and the suggestion is that they&#39;ve helped moderate climate change."
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 549440.0,
      "end_time": 550680.0,
      "text": "Great for us, right?"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 551360.0,
      "end_time": 555960.0,
      "text": "But Waltham showed that if the moon were just a few miles bigger,"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 555120.0,
      "end_time": 556736.0,
      "text": "things would be different."
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 556760.0,
      "end_time": 560960.0,
      "text": "Earth&#39;s spin axis would now wander chaotically."
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 560120.0,
      "end_time": 563160.0,
      "text": "There&#39;d be episodes of rapid climate change --"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 563400.0,
      "end_time": 565415.0,
      "text": "not good for complex life."
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 565440.0,
      "end_time": 567656.0,
      "text": "The moon is just the right size:"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 567680.0,
      "end_time": 570736.0,
      "text": "big but not too big."
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 570760.0,
      "end_time": 573176.0,
      "text": "A \"Goldilocks\" moon around a \"Goldilocks\" planet --"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 573200.0,
      "end_time": 574720.0,
      "text": "a barrier perhaps."
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 575200.0,
      "end_time": 577160.0,
      "text": "You can imagine more barriers."
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 577400.0,
      "end_time": 578256.0,
      "text": "For instance,"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 578280.0,
      "end_time": 581319.0,
      "text": "simple cells came into being billions of years ago ..."
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 582480.0,
      "end_time": 585776.0,
      "text": "but perhaps the development of complex life"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 585800.0,
      "end_time": 588695.0,
      "text": "needed a series of unlikely events."
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 588720.0,
      "end_time": 591296.0,
      "text": "Once life on Earth had access to multicellularity"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 591320.0,
      "end_time": 593376.0,
      "text": "and sophisticated genetic structures,"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 593400.0,
      "end_time": 594656.0,
      "text": "and sex,"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 594680.0,
      "end_time": 596215.0,
      "text": "new opportunities opened up:"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 596240.0,
      "end_time": 597600.0,
      "text": "animals became possible."
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 598240.0,
      "end_time": 601560.0,
      "text": "But maybe it&#39;s the fate of many planets"
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 601800.0,
      "end_time": 604920.0,
      "text": "for life to settle at the level of simple cells."
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 606760.0,
      "end_time": 609856.0,
      "text": "Purely for the purposes of illustration,"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 609880.0,
      "end_time": 612936.0,
      "text": "let me suggest four more barriers to add to the four"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 612960.0,
      "end_time": 616880.0,
      "text": "that people said blocked the path to communicative civilization."
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 617760.0,
      "end_time": 621160.0,
      "text": "Again, purely for the purposes of illustration,"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 621400.0,
      "end_time": 625295.0,
      "text": "suppose there&#39;s a one-in-a-thousand chance of making it across each of the barriers."
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 625320.0,
      "end_time": 628456.0,
      "text": "Of course there might be different ways of navigating the barriers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 628480.0,
      "end_time": 631256.0,
      "text": "and some chances will be better than one in a thousand."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 631280.0,
      "end_time": 633136.0,
      "text": "Equally, there might be more barriers"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 633160.0,
      "end_time": 635415.0,
      "text": "and some chances might be one in a million."
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 635440.0,
      "end_time": 637520.0,
      "text": "Let&#39;s just see what happens in this picture."
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 639120.0,
      "end_time": 641696.0,
      "text": "If the galaxy contains a trillion planets,"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 641720.0,
      "end_time": 647216.0,
      "text": "how many will host a civilization capable of contemplating like us"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 647240.0,
      "end_time": 649440.0,
      "text": "projects such as Breakthrough Starshot?"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 650480.0,
      "end_time": 651736.0,
      "text": "Habitability --"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 651760.0,
      "end_time": 654576.0,
      "text": "right sort of planet around the right sort of star --"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 654600.0,
      "end_time": 656936.0,
      "text": "the trillion becomes a billion."
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 656960.0,
      "end_time": 658296.0,
      "text": "Stability --"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 658320.0,
      "end_time": 661736.0,
      "text": "a climate that stays benign for eons --"
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 661760.0,
      "end_time": 663616.0,
      "text": "the billion becomes a million."
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 663640.0,
      "end_time": 664840.0,
      "text": "Life must start --"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 665600.0,
      "end_time": 667816.0,
      "text": "the million becomes a thousand."
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 667840.0,
      "end_time": 670960.0,
      "text": "Complex life forms must arise --"
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 670120.0,
      "end_time": 672696.0,
      "text": "the thousand becomes one."
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 672720.0,
      "end_time": 674576.0,
      "text": "Sophisticated tool use must develop --"
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 674600.0,
      "end_time": 676600.0,
      "text": "that&#39;s one planet in a thousand galaxies."
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 677480.0,
      "end_time": 679560.0,
      "text": "To understand the universe,"
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 679800.0,
      "end_time": 682296.0,
      "text": "they&#39;ll have to develop the techniques of science and mathematics --"
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 682320.0,
      "end_time": 684416.0,
      "text": "that&#39;s one planet in a million galaxies."
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 684440.0,
      "end_time": 687960.0,
      "text": "To reach the stars, they&#39;ll have to be social creatures,"
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 687120.0,
      "end_time": 689936.0,
      "text": "capable of discussing abstract concepts with each other"
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 689960.0,
      "end_time": 691856.0,
      "text": "using complex grammar --"
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 691880.0,
      "end_time": 695960.0,
      "text": "one planet in a billion galaxies."
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 695120.0,
      "end_time": 696856.0,
      "text": "And they have to avoid disaster --"
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 696880.0,
      "end_time": 700936.0,
      "text": "not just self-inflicted but from the skies, too."
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 700960.0,
      "end_time": 703896.0,
      "text": "That planet around Proxima Centauri,"
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 703920.0,
      "end_time": 706240.0,
      "text": "last year it got blasted by a flare."
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 707200.0,
      "end_time": 709136.0,
      "text": "One planet in a trillion galaxies,"
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 709160.0,
      "end_time": 711920.0,
      "text": "just as in the visible universe."
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 714480.0,
      "end_time": 715680.0,
      "text": "I think we&#39;re alone."
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 717240.0,
      "end_time": 719536.0,
      "text": "Those colleagues of mine who agree we&#39;re alone"
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 719560.0,
      "end_time": 722695.0,
      "text": "often see a barrier ahead --"
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 722720.0,
      "end_time": 723976.0,
      "text": "bioterror,"
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 724000.0,
      "end_time": 725560.0,
      "text": "global warming, war."
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 726320.0,
      "end_time": 729336.0,
      "text": "A universe that&#39;s silent"
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 729360.0,
      "end_time": 732776.0,
      "text": "because technology itself forms the barrier"
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 732800.0,
      "end_time": 736736.0,
      "text": "to the development of a truly advanced civilization."
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 736760.0,
      "end_time": 738200.0,
      "text": "Depressing, right?"
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 739240.0,
      "end_time": 740920.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m arguing the exact opposite."
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 742560.0,
      "end_time": 745136.0,
      "text": "I grew up watching \"Star Trek\" and \"Forbidden Planet,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 745160.0,
      "end_time": 746935.0,
      "text": "and I saw a UFO once,"
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 746960.0,
      "end_time": 753400.0,
      "text": "so this idea of cosmic loneliness I certainly find slightly wistful."
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 754240.0,
      "end_time": 756336.0,
      "text": "But for me,"
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 756360.0,
      "end_time": 758296.0,
      "text": "the silence of the universe is shouting,"
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 758320.0,
      "end_time": 760400.0,
      "text": "\"We&#39;re the creatures who got lucky.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 760800.0,
      "end_time": 762656.0,
      "text": "All barriers are behind us."
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 762680.0,
      "end_time": 765960.0,
      "text": "We&#39;re the only species that&#39;s cleared them --"
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 765120.0,
      "end_time": 769536.0,
      "text": "the only species capable of determining its own destiny."
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 769560.0,
      "end_time": 772760.0,
      "text": "And if we learn to appreciate how special our planet is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 773840.0,
      "end_time": 775976.0,
      "text": "how important it is to look after our home"
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 776000.0,
      "end_time": 777816.0,
      "text": "and to find others,"
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 777840.0,
      "end_time": 782656.0,
      "text": "how incredibly fortunate we all are simply to be aware of the universe,"
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 782680.0,
      "end_time": 785160.0,
      "text": "humanity might survive for a while."
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 785400.0,
      "end_time": 786695.0,
      "text": "And all those amazing things"
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 786720.0,
      "end_time": 789576.0,
      "text": "we dreamed aliens might have done in the past,"
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 789600.0,
      "end_time": 790800.0,
      "text": "that could be our future."
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
      "start_time": 791640.0,
      "end_time": 792896.0,
      "text": "Thank you very much."
    },
    {
      "index": 270,
      "start_time": 792920.0,
      "end_time": 796439.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}